# 🧪 AWS VPC + EC2 + Website Hosting – Terraform Lab

**Service Used:** Amazon VPC, EC2, Terraform

---

# 🔷 Lab Architecture Flow

```
Create VPC
    ↓
Create Public Subnet
    ↓
Attach Internet Gateway
    ↓
Create Route Table → IGW
    ↓
Associate Subnet
    ↓
Create Security Group (22, 80)
    ↓
Create Key Pair
    ↓
Launch EC2 Instance
    ↓
Install Apache using User Data
    ↓
Deploy Website
    ↓
Access via Public IP
```

---

# 📌 Lab Objective

In this lab, we will:

* Create a custom VPC
* Configure public subnet with internet access
* Launch EC2 instance using Terraform
* Install Apache web server automatically
* Host a static website
* Access application via browser

---

# 🏗️ Architecture Details

| Component     | Value               |
| ------------- | ------------------- |
| VPC CIDR      | 10.0.0.0/16         |
| Subnet        | 10.0.1.0/24         |
| Region        | ap-south-1          |
| Instance Type | t3.micro            |
| OS            | Amazon Linux 2      |
| Ports         | 22 (SSH), 80 (HTTP) |

---

# ⚙️ Terraform Configuration

## 🔹 Provider

```hcl
provider "aws" {
  region = "ap-south-1"
}
```

---

## 🔹 VPC

```hcl
resource "aws_vpc" "main" {
  cidr_block = "10.0.0.0/16"

  tags = {
    Name = "my-vpc"
  }
}
```

---

## 🔹 Public Subnet

```hcl
resource "aws_subnet" "public" {
  vpc_id                  = aws_vpc.main.id
  cidr_block              = "10.0.1.0/24"
  availability_zone       = "ap-south-1a"
  map_public_ip_on_launch = true
}
```

---

## 🔹 Internet Gateway

```hcl
resource "aws_internet_gateway" "igw" {
  vpc_id = aws_vpc.main.id
}
```

---

## 🔹 Route Table

```hcl
resource "aws_route_table" "public_rt" {
  vpc_id = aws_vpc.main.id

  route {
    cidr_block = "0.0.0.0/0"
    gateway_id = aws_internet_gateway.igw.id
  }
}
```

---

## 🔹 Route Table Association

```hcl
resource "aws_route_table_association" "assoc" {
  subnet_id      = aws_subnet.public.id
  route_table_id = aws_route_table.public_rt.id
}
```

---

## 🔹 Security Group

```hcl
resource "aws_security_group" "ec2_sg" {
  vpc_id = aws_vpc.main.id

  ingress {
    from_port   = 22
    to_port     = 22
    protocol    = "tcp"
    cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"]
  }

  ingress {
    from_port   = 80
    to_port     = 80
    protocol    = "tcp"
    cidr_blocks = ["0.0.0.0/0"]
  }
}
```

---

## 🔹 Key Pair

```hcl
resource "aws_key_pair" "key" {
  key_name   = "terraform-key"
  public_key = file("C:/Users/HP/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub")
}
```

---

## 🔹 EC2 Instance + Website

```hcl
resource "aws_instance" "example" {
  ami           = data.aws_ami.amazon_linux.id
  instance_type = "t3.micro"

  subnet_id              = aws_subnet.public.id
  vpc_security_group_ids = [aws_security_group.ec2_sg.id]
  key_name               = aws_key_pair.key.key_name

  associate_public_ip_address = true

  user_data = <<-EOF
              #!/bin/bash
              yum update -y
              yum install -y httpd
              systemctl start httpd
              systemctl enable httpd

              echo "<h1>Welcome Suresh - DevOps Engineer</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html
              EOF
}
```

